HEADWORD: Iridic
<hw>I*rid"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
the iris of the eye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iridic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Iridic
<hw>I*rid"ic</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to iridium; -- said specifically of those compounds in which
iridium has a relatively high valence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

